headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 24 points and 10 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks swept the four-game season series with Charlotte, beating the Hornets 111-99 on Thursday night to finish a home-and-home set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis Antetokounmpo scores 24 points, Bucks beat Hornets 111-99 to sweep season series

headlines.description: — Jalen Suggs hit three 3-pointers in the final three minutes and finished with 15 points as the Orlando Magic beat the Utah Jazz 115-107 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Suggs and Paolo Banchero lead the Magic to a 115-107 win over the slumping Jazz

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson scored a season high 29 points, hitting a season-high seven 3-pointers in 11 attempts, to help the Brooklyn Nets beat the Atlanta Hawks 124-97 on Thursday night to open a two-game series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Johnson scores season-high 29 points to help Nets rout Hawks 124-97

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — A much better start for Stephen Curry led to one of the best in the NBA this season for the Golden State Warriors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry has 31 points and 11 rebounds, leads Warriors to 110-99 victory over Knicks

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — San Antonio rookie sensation Victor Wembanyama punctuated snapping a five-game skid by shouting an explicative into a live house microphone to let Spurs fans know how much he missed playing in front of them.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama, Spurs beat Thunder 132-118 to snap 5-game skid

headlines.description: — Phoenix All-Star Devin Booker and Houston rookie Cam Whitmore got into a minor scuffle midway through the fourth quarter Thursday night and both players were called for a technical foul.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 35 points, Kevin Durant adds 24 to help the Suns beat the Rockets, 110-105

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. had 30 points to help pick up the scoring load after Jamal Murray left because of a sprained ankle, and the Denver Nuggets staved off Miami's fourth-quarter rally to beat the Heat 103-97 <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter scores 30 points, Nuggets hold off Heat's 4th-quarter rally in 103-97 victory

events.name: Washington Wizards at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 40 points and 15 rebounds, LeBron James added 31 points and Los Angeles extended the Washington Wizards' losing streak to 13 games with a 134-131 victory Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers send the Wizards to their 13th straight loss with a 134-131 overtime victory
